1
00:00:35,041 --> 00:00:38,841
(FAINT GROWLING)

2
00:00:38,961 --> 00:00:40,321
DOCTOR: Great work, guys.

3
00:00:40,441 --> 00:00:42,001
- And sorry again.
- (CREATURE SCREECHES)

4
00:00:42,121 --> 00:00:44,561
I did not know
it was their mating season.

5
00:00:44,681 --> 00:00:46,241
Yes, Graham, my son!
I've got it!

6
00:00:46,361 --> 00:00:47,401
Got what?

7
00:00:47,521 --> 00:00:49,481
The sixth coupon
from the Bandohzi Herald.

8
00:00:49,601 --> 00:00:51,081
Keeps getting delivered
by the coffee machine upstairs.

9
00:00:51,201 --> 00:00:52,121
Or is it downstairs?

10
00:00:52,241 --> 00:00:56,001
Anyway, don't matter.
I noticed they had an offer on.

11
00:00:56,121 --> 00:00:58,641
Collect six coupons,
get a free holiday.

12
00:00:58,761 --> 00:00:59,961
I'm up for a free holiday.

13
00:01:00,081 --> 00:01:02,441
- Where is it?
- A place called Tranquillity.

14
00:01:02,561 --> 00:01:04,041
Me too. So long as
there's plenty of sun

15
00:01:04,161 --> 00:01:06,481
and absolutely
no deep-space squid.

16
00:01:06,601 --> 00:01:08,041
Might get you
out of your mardy mood.

17
00:01:09,081 --> 00:01:10,081
My mood's fine.

18
00:01:10,201 --> 00:01:12,401
- That's you told.
- (WHIRRING)

19
00:01:12,521 --> 00:01:13,881
DOCTOR: Hang on, Graham.
They're not

20
00:01:14,001 --> 00:01:15,081
six perfect squares, are they?

21
00:01:15,201 --> 00:01:16,881
No, don't put them together
yet!

22
00:01:17,001 --> 00:01:18,761
- RYAN: Bit late for that.
- What's happening?

23
00:01:18,881 --> 00:01:20,801
I hope you've packed.
They're not just coupons.

24
00:01:20,921 --> 00:01:22,561
That's a teleport cube -
just activated.

25
00:01:22,681 --> 00:01:24,001
We've got about four seconds.

26
00:01:24,121 --> 00:01:26,041
No, no, no, no. I've got to go
and fetch my Speedos.

27
00:01:27,801 --> 00:01:30,041
Only joking.
Already got 'em on. Ho-ho!

28
00:01:34,841 --> 00:01:36,961
TANNOY:
Welcome to Tranquillity Spa.

29
00:01:37,081 --> 00:01:39,601
Oh, guys! This is a bit
of all right, innit?

30
00:01:39,721 --> 00:01:40,641
Welcome!

31
00:01:40,761 --> 00:01:43,481
O'Brien party of four?

32
00:01:43,601 --> 00:01:45,481
Bandohzi Herald coupons?

33
00:01:45,601 --> 00:01:47,121
I'm Hyph3n with a 3,

34
00:01:47,241 --> 00:01:50,441
your customer host here
at Tranquillity Spa.

35
00:01:50,561 --> 00:01:52,441
And relax!

36
00:01:52,561 --> 00:01:53,841
Hi, Hyph3n with a 3. Nice tail.

37
00:01:53,961 --> 00:01:56,441
I'm a bit worried about
being separated from my ship.

38
00:01:56,561 --> 00:01:59,041
Our system has saved
exactly where you came from.

39
00:01:59,161 --> 00:02:01,561
You can return any time, but
you're booked in for two weeks,

40
00:02:01,681 --> 00:02:03,001
all-inclusive.

41
00:02:03,121 --> 00:02:04,041
Get in!

42
00:02:04,161 --> 00:02:06,041
Your rooms
are just being prepared.

43
00:02:06,161 --> 00:02:07,481
Take a moment to explore

44
00:02:07,601 --> 00:02:09,441
and I'll come and find you
once they're ready.

45
00:02:09,561 --> 00:02:10,921
I'm going to find the pool!

46
00:02:11,041 --> 00:02:12,681
I'm seeing what they've got
inside the building.

47
00:02:12,801 --> 00:02:15,881
And I am going to sit
over there for three hours,

48
00:02:16,001 --> 00:02:18,921
then I'm going to get up
and sit somewhere else,

49
00:02:19,041 --> 00:02:20,881
and then cocktails.
All-inclusive, Doc.

50
00:02:21,001 --> 00:02:23,321
Got to get your coupons' worth.
Get in!

51
00:02:23,441 --> 00:02:25,601
Come on, Graham, son!

52
00:02:25,721 --> 00:02:27,561
I'll have a look round, then.

53
00:02:27,681 --> 00:02:29,361
By myself.

54
00:02:37,281 --> 00:02:39,921
Relax.
Our staff are being informed.

55
00:02:40,041 --> 00:02:41,961
(ALARM BEEPS)

56
00:02:42,081 --> 00:02:43,441
- Another system virus.
- Vorm, I don't care.

57
00:02:43,561 --> 00:02:44,841
We've got a physical breach.

58
00:02:44,961 --> 00:02:46,281
One of them's got in.

59
00:02:46,401 --> 00:02:49,201
Find it, contain it,
and radio in.

60
00:02:49,321 --> 00:02:50,321
Do not engage without me.

61
00:02:57,361 --> 00:03:00,481
Look at that, Vilma.
Can you believe it?

62
00:03:00,601 --> 00:03:03,201
Oh, it's perfect, Benni.

63
00:03:03,321 --> 00:03:04,841
Thank you.

64
00:03:04,961 --> 00:03:08,121
BENNI: I saw some newlyweds
up at reception.

65
00:03:08,241 --> 00:03:10,081
Nice place to come
for a honeymoon.

66
00:03:10,201 --> 00:03:12,841
We've had 46 years.

67
00:03:12,961 --> 00:03:14,641
We never needed to be married.

68
00:03:14,761 --> 00:03:16,681
You say that...

69
00:03:16,801 --> 00:03:17,761
...but...

70
00:03:17,881 --> 00:03:19,121
Wow!

71
00:03:19,241 --> 00:03:22,041
- BENNI: Oh, hello.
- VILMA: Not bad, is it?

72
00:03:22,161 --> 00:03:23,681
It's absolutely gorgeous.

73
00:03:23,801 --> 00:03:24,841
Um...

74
00:03:24,961 --> 00:03:26,281
YAZ: This place
has got everything.

75
00:03:27,641 --> 00:03:31,961
Welcome to Tranquillity's bar
and refreshment zone.

76
00:03:32,081 --> 00:03:34,721
We serve all your favourites,
all-inclusive.

77
00:03:34,841 --> 00:03:36,281
Oh, free stuff!

78
00:03:39,401 --> 00:03:40,721
- (NUMBER PAD BEEPS)
- Ooh

79
00:03:40,841 --> 00:03:42,521
- (FIZZING)
- Ow! Ow!

80
00:03:42,641 --> 00:03:44,001
Fighting with
the vending machine?

81
00:03:44,121 --> 00:03:45,681
No, it just gave me
an electric shock.

82
00:03:45,801 --> 00:03:47,241
That's not a shock.

83
00:03:47,361 --> 00:03:48,801
It's a hopper virus.

84
00:03:48,921 --> 00:03:49,841
This machine's sick,

85
00:03:49,961 --> 00:03:51,121
and it just passed its virus on
to you.

86
00:03:51,241 --> 00:03:52,881
How did I get a virus the same
as a vending machine?

87
00:03:53,001 --> 00:03:53,961
I'm not a machine.

88
00:03:54,081 --> 00:03:56,121
Hoppers are multi-platform.
They'll go for anything.

89
00:03:56,241 --> 00:03:57,961
- Don't pick at it!
- Did it just go through me?

90
00:03:58,081 --> 00:03:59,001
It's moving deeper inside you

91
00:03:59,121 --> 00:04:00,321
to mutate
into your nervous system.

92
00:04:00,441 --> 00:04:01,361
What?

93
00:04:01,481 --> 00:04:02,481
Important not to panic.

94
00:04:02,601 --> 00:04:04,441
Humans always have the same
reaction to a hopper virus.

95
00:04:04,561 --> 00:04:05,761
First you get
the wiggly fingers,

96
00:04:05,881 --> 00:04:07,521
which is a warning
the legs are about to go.

97
00:04:07,641 --> 00:04:08,361
Luckily,

98
00:04:08,481 --> 00:04:10,321
this is where my hopper
first-aid training kicks in.

99
00:04:12,561 --> 00:04:13,881
Need to get rid of these.

100
00:04:14,001 --> 00:04:16,041
Then pinch your ear.

101
00:04:16,161 --> 00:04:18,041
- Then you're going to sneeze.
- Atchoo!

102
00:04:18,161 --> 00:04:22,121
Yes! Now suck your thumb
until the hallucinations stop.

103
00:04:22,241 --> 00:04:23,881
And remember,
they're not real bats.

104
00:04:25,161 --> 00:04:27,361
- (RYAN SQUEALS)
- He's fine.

105
00:04:27,481 --> 00:04:29,081
He's fine.

106
00:04:30,761 --> 00:04:31,841
Make the bats go away!

107
00:04:31,961 --> 00:04:33,121
Hotel perimeter breach.

108
00:04:33,241 --> 00:04:35,241
Initiating guest
protection measures.

109
00:04:35,361 --> 00:04:36,481
It's on the move again, Vorm.

110
00:04:36,601 --> 00:04:38,641
Be careful.

111
00:04:38,761 --> 00:04:40,801
I'm Vilma. Nice to meet you.

112
00:04:40,921 --> 00:04:42,241
This is Benni.

113
00:04:42,361 --> 00:04:44,521
Yaz. Just arrived.

114
00:04:44,641 --> 00:04:45,641
Sorry, I didn't mean
to interrupt.

115
00:04:45,761 --> 00:04:47,801
- Oh, you're all right...
- Well, you were a bit...

116
00:04:47,921 --> 00:04:50,521
All guests, please assemble
at your nearest muster station.

117
00:04:50,641 --> 00:04:52,281
Relax.

118
00:04:52,401 --> 00:04:55,201
This is a routine
Tranquillity drill.

119
00:04:55,321 --> 00:04:58,441
All guests, please assemble
at your nearest muster station.

120
00:04:58,561 --> 00:05:00,601
If this is anything to do
with you, Doc...

121
00:05:00,721 --> 00:05:01,681
Relax.

122
00:05:01,801 --> 00:05:03,201
This is a routine
Tranquillity drill.

123
00:05:03,321 --> 00:05:05,841
Stay here. I'll investigate.
It's probably nothing.

124
00:05:05,961 --> 00:05:07,521
Usually nothing.

125
00:05:07,641 --> 00:05:09,321
I say "usually”...

126
00:05:09,441 --> 00:05:14,041
All guests, please assemble
at your nearest muster station.

127
00:05:14,161 --> 00:05:18,601
The nearest muster station to
this zone is the teleport pad.

128
00:05:19,761 --> 00:05:22,721
Hopper virus got you too?

129
00:05:24,001 --> 00:05:26,281
I'm not sure about this place.

130
00:05:28,121 --> 00:05:29,521
So...

131
00:05:30,561 --> 00:05:31,881
...you here with family?

132
00:05:34,881 --> 00:05:36,241
Hotel critic.

133
00:05:36,361 --> 00:05:37,921
Mm.

134
00:05:38,041 --> 00:05:39,001
You?

135
00:05:39,121 --> 00:05:42,481
Oh, I'm here with my mates,
yeah.

136
00:05:42,601 --> 00:05:44,841
I'm a pilot...surgeon...
pilot...surgeon...

137
00:05:44,961 --> 00:05:46,881
I'm a surgeon for pilots.

138
00:05:47,001 --> 00:05:51,041
So, do you come across
many hopper viruses?

139
00:05:51,161 --> 00:05:52,721
Does this usually work?

140
00:05:52,841 --> 00:05:54,281
- What?
- Pretending to be stupid

141
00:05:54,401 --> 00:05:55,761
so girls have to answer
your questions?

142
00:05:55,881 --> 00:05:58,321
Hey, look, I'm not
trying to chat you up.

143
00:06:00,881 --> 00:06:02,521
Shame.

144
00:06:04,841 --> 00:06:06,841
I'm Bella.

145
00:06:08,161 --> 00:06:09,161
Oh...

146
00:06:09,281 --> 00:06:10,441
VORM: Heading to the east zone.

147
00:06:10,561 --> 00:06:11,921
I'll isolate it there.

148
00:06:13,761 --> 00:06:17,361
If this is a drill,
what's he doing with a gun?

149
00:06:19,641 --> 00:06:21,321
Do you want to find out?

150
00:06:22,921 --> 00:06:26,001
Relax. This is a routine
Tranquillity drill.

151
00:06:26,121 --> 00:06:27,481
Coming up to linen cupboard
now.

152
00:06:27,601 --> 00:06:29,201
Hyph3n with a 3!

153
00:06:29,321 --> 00:06:31,561
I just pulled this
out of a friend of mine.

154
00:06:31,681 --> 00:06:34,121
Well, we do not make any
judgments on our guests

155
00:06:34,241 --> 00:06:36,401
and fully support any way
you choose to enjoy yourself

156
00:06:36,521 --> 00:06:37,561
here at Tranquillity Spa.

157
00:06:37,681 --> 00:06:39,921
It wasn't recreational.
This is a weapon.

158
00:06:40,041 --> 00:06:41,601
I'd say someone
is targeting you.

159
00:06:41,721 --> 00:06:42,841
Now, why would they do that?

160
00:06:42,961 --> 00:06:44,961
Also, why is that alarm
going off?

161
00:06:45,081 --> 00:06:46,161
And why do you look
so concerned?

162
00:06:46,281 --> 00:06:47,761
Also, where does the 3
come in "Hyphen"?

163
00:06:47,881 --> 00:06:49,481
Never mind. That one can wait.

164
00:06:49,601 --> 00:06:52,041
Also... Also,
what's behind that door?

165
00:06:52,161 --> 00:06:53,601
Cos no linen cupboard
needs a key

166
00:06:53,721 --> 00:06:55,321
with that many
security gradings.

167
00:06:55,441 --> 00:06:56,361
I want to take a look.

168
00:06:56,481 --> 00:06:59,161
Guests aren't permitted
in the...linen cupboard.

169
00:06:59,281 --> 00:07:00,841
How about...

170
00:07:00,961 --> 00:07:03,721
...Pan-galactic Standards
and Practices Officer?

171
00:07:03,841 --> 00:07:05,401
Health and Safety?

172
00:07:05,521 --> 00:07:07,761
Security and Hygiene?

173
00:07:07,881 --> 00:07:08,921
Resort Inspector?

174
00:07:09,041 --> 00:07:11,601
Now, are you
and your excellent tail

175
00:07:11,721 --> 00:07:12,921
going to let me have a look,

176
00:07:13,041 --> 00:07:15,601
or am I going to have
to bark at you? Cos I will.

177
00:07:18,001 --> 00:07:18,921
(BEEP)

178
00:07:19,041 --> 00:07:20,801
It's after the second H
and before the final N.

179
00:07:20,921 --> 00:07:22,681
- The 3.
- Oh, yeah!

180
00:07:22,801 --> 00:07:24,081
Course.

181
00:07:27,241 --> 00:07:30,001
Deadlocked room
with its own armoury.

182
00:07:30,121 --> 00:07:32,721
Don't tell me. Honeymoon suite?

183
00:07:32,841 --> 00:07:34,521
Hyph3n, what the hell
are you doing?

184
00:07:34,641 --> 00:07:35,441
Who's this?

185
00:07:35,561 --> 00:07:38,201
I'm the Doctor, and you, madam,
are far too handsy.

186
00:07:38,321 --> 00:07:39,321
Resort Inspector.

187
00:07:39,441 --> 00:07:40,841
We've only just been inspected.

188
00:07:40,961 --> 00:07:43,201
Well, we like to surprise.
Just like this hopper virus

189
00:07:43,321 --> 00:07:44,601
I found
in your vending machine.

190
00:07:44,721 --> 00:07:47,441
This will mutate any system
it hops into and wreck it.

191
00:07:47,561 --> 00:07:48,801
This is part of a family set,

192
00:07:48,921 --> 00:07:51,921
so there are other replications
out there, which might explain

193
00:07:52,041 --> 00:07:53,961
why your ionic membrane's
failed.

194
00:07:55,641 --> 00:07:57,481
why would you need
to defend a holiday spa

195
00:07:57,601 --> 00:07:59,961
with an ionic membrane?

196
00:08:00,241 --> 00:08:01,161
(DOOR UNLOCKS)

197
00:08:01,281 --> 00:08:03,801
Power systems
in this zone of Tranquillity

198
00:08:03,921 --> 00:08:05,481
are currently
experiencing challenges.

199
00:08:05,601 --> 00:08:07,441
(CLATTERING)

200
00:08:09,401 --> 00:08:10,921
(GROWLING)

201
00:08:11,041 --> 00:08:12,441
Help me!

202
00:08:12,561 --> 00:08:14,921
- Relax, and leave immediately.
- Please!

203
00:08:15,041 --> 00:08:16,641
- Please!
- Confirmed sighting.

204
00:08:16,761 --> 00:08:18,161
It's on the loose inside.

205
00:08:18,281 --> 00:08:19,641
(SNARLING)

206
00:08:19,761 --> 00:08:21,681
It's attacking the guests.

207
00:08:21,801 --> 00:08:25,001
What did he say?
What's attacking the guests?

208
00:08:25,121 --> 00:08:26,681
Why do you need all this?
Tell me.

209
00:08:26,801 --> 00:08:28,241
Do not engage. I'm en route.

210
00:08:28,361 --> 00:08:30,201
We have to implement
teleport evacuation procedures.

211
00:08:30,321 --> 00:08:31,641
Don't tell me about
the procedures, Hyph3n.

212
00:08:31,761 --> 00:08:32,681
I wrote them.

213
00:08:32,801 --> 00:08:34,241
You can forget
about evacuation.

214
00:08:34,361 --> 00:08:36,361
The hopper virus
is in your teleport system.

215
00:08:36,481 --> 00:08:37,401
Everything's down.

216
00:08:37,521 --> 00:08:39,561
I need you here to help me
understand this place,

217
00:08:39,681 --> 00:08:42,241
not out there
shooting at things.

218
00:08:44,281 --> 00:08:46,281
This zone of Tranquillity
ls compromised.

219
00:08:46,401 --> 00:08:50,161
If you can hear this message,
you shouldn't be here.

220
00:08:50,281 --> 00:08:51,921
Leave immediately.

221
00:08:52,041 --> 00:08:54,081
- (SNARLS)
- Stay back!

222
00:08:58,481 --> 00:08:59,681
(ELECTRICAL FIZZING)

223
00:09:01,961 --> 00:09:04,681
Kane, there's more than one.
I have to retreat!

224
00:09:04,801 --> 00:09:06,401
(SNARLING)

225
00:09:07,401 --> 00:09:09,441
- RYAN: Something's down there.
- BELLA: In here.

226
00:09:10,561 --> 00:09:12,161
Good, here we go.
You're maintenance, right?

227
00:09:12,281 --> 00:09:13,401
You're just the fella.

228
00:09:13,521 --> 00:09:16,321
You are needed outside.

229
00:09:16,441 --> 00:09:17,601
Some of the guests reckon that

230
00:09:17,721 --> 00:09:18,921
the teleport on the terrace
ain't working.

231
00:09:19,041 --> 00:09:21,761
Yeah, nothing's working,
mate, sorry.

232
00:09:21,881 --> 00:09:23,681
Where's my snap hammer?

233
00:09:23,801 --> 00:09:25,641
Sylas?

234
00:09:25,761 --> 00:09:28,561
Snap hammer won't fix that.
You want a crash wrench.

235
00:09:28,681 --> 00:09:31,641
Oi, you're not a mechanic.
You're a child.

236
00:09:31,761 --> 00:09:33,281
Now pass me the snap hammer.

237
00:09:33,401 --> 00:09:35,801
I'm Nevi. This is my boy Sylas.

238
00:09:35,921 --> 00:09:36,881
All right, Sylas?

239
00:09:37,001 --> 00:09:38,641
Yeah, he likes to show up
without warning.

240
00:09:38,761 --> 00:09:40,801
This place is way better
than Mum's house.

241
00:09:42,281 --> 00:09:43,321
How many people
have you got staying here?

242
00:09:43,441 --> 00:09:45,881
23. This shows
all their positions.

243
00:09:46,001 --> 00:09:47,441
- Guest offline.
- No, 21 now.

244
00:09:47,561 --> 00:09:50,001
Guest online. Guest off...

245
00:09:50,121 --> 00:09:51,281
- (SNARLING)
- (SCREAMS)

246
00:09:51,401 --> 00:09:53,041
- 19.
- ...offline.

247
00:09:53,161 --> 00:09:55,001
Guest offline. Guest offline.

248
00:09:55,121 --> 00:09:56,641
Our friends are out there.

249
00:09:56,761 --> 00:09:59,281
All guests
within the hotel building,

250
00:09:59,401 --> 00:10:02,161
to the linen cupboard in
the north corridor immediately.

251
00:10:02,281 --> 00:10:03,281
It's just a drill.

252
00:10:03,401 --> 00:10:05,401
Not a drill.

253
00:10:05,521 --> 00:10:06,721
Repeat, not a drill.

254
00:10:06,841 --> 00:10:09,121
I'm sure it's nothing
to worry about.

255
00:10:09,241 --> 00:10:11,401
(SNARLING AND SCREAMING)

256
00:10:11,521 --> 00:10:14,561
(SCREAMS REVERBERATE)

257
00:10:14,681 --> 00:10:17,321
We should probably
head to the linen cupboard.

258
00:10:17,441 --> 00:10:18,801
Guest offline.

259
00:10:18,921 --> 00:10:21,001
DOCTOR:
Where's your security team?

260
00:10:21,121 --> 00:10:22,761
KANE: No team.
Just me and Vorm.

261
00:10:22,881 --> 00:10:23,801
(SNARLING)

262
00:10:23,921 --> 00:10:27,081
This zone of Tranquillity
ls compromised.

263
00:10:27,201 --> 00:10:29,681
Please do not enter
the Tranquillity steam room

264
00:10:29,801 --> 00:10:31,361
during this routine drill.

265
00:10:31,481 --> 00:10:33,041
MAN: Help! Please, it's coming!

266
00:10:33,161 --> 00:10:34,601
- RYAN: Hey, what's out there?
- It's seen me!

267
00:10:34,721 --> 00:10:36,561
- What...?
- BELLA: Shut up!

268
00:10:36,681 --> 00:10:38,481
Welcome to the Tranquillity
steam room.

269
00:10:38,601 --> 00:10:40,281
Please leave immediately.

270
00:10:40,401 --> 00:10:42,121
(SNARLING)

271
00:10:42,241 --> 00:10:44,001
Hey.

272
00:10:44,121 --> 00:10:46,481
- I'm not a surgeon for pilots.
- (FAINT SCREAMS)

273
00:10:46,601 --> 00:10:48,201
I work in a warehouse.

274
00:10:48,321 --> 00:10:49,841
I'm not a hotel critic.

275
00:10:49,961 --> 00:10:52,401
I just... I didn't want to say
"unemployed nobody".

276
00:10:52,521 --> 00:10:53,921
(SCREAMING)

277
00:10:54,041 --> 00:10:55,041
(SNARLS)

278
00:10:55,161 --> 00:10:59,281
An unauthorised life form
has entered the steam room.

279
00:11:00,921 --> 00:11:03,201
This debug script should
neutralise the hopper viruses,

280
00:11:03,321 --> 00:11:04,521
but they'll need time to work.

281
00:11:04,641 --> 00:11:08,041
More urgently, I need to build
a new ionic membrane

282
00:11:08,161 --> 00:11:09,881
to banish whatever is killing
your guests.

283
00:11:10,001 --> 00:11:12,321
You can't build an ionic
membrane from scratch.

284
00:11:12,441 --> 00:11:13,881
If I had crayons
and half a can of Spam,

285
00:11:14,001 --> 00:11:16,041
I could build you from scratch.
Now, out of my way.

286
00:11:19,601 --> 00:11:21,401
HYPH3N: They'll take
the bodies, won't they?

287
00:11:21,521 --> 00:11:24,361
There you are. We heard the
Doctor's voice over the Tannoy.

288
00:11:24,481 --> 00:11:26,521
Also gunfire.
And people screaming.

289
00:11:26,641 --> 00:11:28,201
Yeah, I know.
I've been on better holidays.

290
00:11:28,321 --> 00:11:30,641
All of you, in here.

291
00:11:33,281 --> 00:11:34,881
That's a funny kind
of linen cupboard.

292
00:11:35,001 --> 00:11:36,601
Hi, can't talk. Building.

293
00:11:38,401 --> 00:11:40,201
Always the hat, Vilma.

294
00:11:42,161 --> 00:11:45,041
(GROWLING)

295
00:11:45,161 --> 00:11:47,601
KANE: I'm losing visuals
across the compound.

296
00:11:47,721 --> 00:11:49,881
I don't know how many
of those creatures have got in.

297
00:11:50,001 --> 00:11:52,361
Kane, I'm sorry.
I couldn't stop it.

298
00:11:52,481 --> 00:11:54,441
It's your job to stop it, Vorm.

299
00:11:57,241 --> 00:12:00,841
VORM: Those things are heading
for the guest teleport.

300
00:12:02,601 --> 00:12:04,401
Benni, I dropped my hat.

301
00:12:07,121 --> 00:12:08,921
Where's Benni?

302
00:12:09,041 --> 00:12:11,041
And where's Ryan?

303
00:12:13,721 --> 00:12:14,841
Shh!

304
00:12:16,081 --> 00:12:17,121
(WHISPERS) Don't run.

305
00:12:17,241 --> 00:12:18,841
Psst.

306
00:12:18,961 --> 00:12:19,921
(PANTS)

307
00:12:20,041 --> 00:12:21,841
- (SNARLS)
- (SCREAMS)

308
00:12:22,961 --> 00:12:24,201
DOCTOR: I got it.

309
00:12:24,321 --> 00:12:25,681
Ionic membrane.

310
00:12:25,801 --> 00:12:27,561
Reinstated DNA filter.

311
00:12:27,681 --> 00:12:29,881
It'll exile any life form
not pre-approved.

312
00:12:30,001 --> 00:12:31,521
If I've built this right.

313
00:12:38,401 --> 00:12:40,041
(THUDDING)

314
00:12:40,161 --> 00:12:41,441
(GROWLS)

315
00:12:41,561 --> 00:12:43,041
(BELLA WHIMPERS)

316
00:12:43,161 --> 00:12:45,961
(SNARLS)

317
00:12:50,961 --> 00:12:53,121
(ROARS)

318
00:12:58,961 --> 00:13:01,241
DOCTOR: Yes. It worked!

319
00:13:01,361 --> 00:13:02,681
Seal is secure.

320
00:13:02,801 --> 00:13:06,161
Internal 02 level
restored to 20.5%.

321
00:13:06,281 --> 00:13:08,161
The ionic membrane's
forced those things out.

322
00:13:10,761 --> 00:13:12,761
Now, open the door.
Our friend's out there.

323
00:13:12,881 --> 00:13:14,441
What are those red dots?

324
00:13:14,561 --> 00:13:15,481
VORM: Casualties of the Dregs.

325
00:13:15,601 --> 00:13:16,601
NEVI: Don't look, Sylas.

326
00:13:18,441 --> 00:13:20,281
BELLA: Has it gone?

327
00:13:21,841 --> 00:13:23,001
What just happened?

328
00:13:24,601 --> 00:13:26,201
If I had to guess...

329
00:13:26,321 --> 00:13:27,641
The Doctor.

330
00:13:30,001 --> 00:13:32,001
GRAHAM: Can you show me Ryan?
Where's Ryan on there?

331
00:13:32,121 --> 00:13:33,401
I'm so sorry.

332
00:13:40,641 --> 00:13:43,841
VILMA: Yaz, I can't see Benni
on there either.

333
00:13:43,961 --> 00:13:45,921
Where's Benni?

334
00:13:47,641 --> 00:13:49,321
GRAHAM: Ryan!

335
00:13:49,441 --> 00:13:51,041
Ryan!

336
00:13:52,601 --> 00:13:54,881
Ryan! Ryan!

337
00:13:55,001 --> 00:13:56,201
- Graham.
- Oh!

338
00:13:56,321 --> 00:13:58,121
What's happening?

339
00:13:58,241 --> 00:13:59,801
Oh, Ryan!

340
00:13:59,921 --> 00:14:01,841
It ain't the aliens
that are gonna kill me,

341
00:14:01,961 --> 00:14:03,361
it's worrying about you.

342
00:14:04,921 --> 00:14:07,041
DOCTOR: What is it
that got in here?

343
00:14:07,161 --> 00:14:08,561
KANE: A couple of the locals.
Dregs.

344
00:14:08,681 --> 00:14:10,041
They're always trying
to attack.

345
00:14:10,161 --> 00:14:11,281
That's why we have shields.

346
00:14:11,401 --> 00:14:13,121
But the virus that brought
the shields down,

347
00:14:13,241 --> 00:14:14,681
the Dregs couldn't have
done that.

348
00:14:14,801 --> 00:14:16,001
Somebody hacked the system.

349
00:14:16,121 --> 00:14:17,561
RYAN: Who'd sabotage a hotel?

350
00:14:17,681 --> 00:14:20,321
KANE: Vorm, void panel SE9-13.

351
00:14:28,721 --> 00:14:30,201
RYAN: What is happening
right now?

352
00:14:30,321 --> 00:14:31,561
- (THUD)
- RYAN: Ooh.

353
00:14:31,681 --> 00:14:34,481
Cor blimey! Right on me nut!

354
00:14:34,601 --> 00:14:36,241
Am I having a stroke
or something?

355
00:14:36,361 --> 00:14:37,721
- It's a fake-cation.
- GRAHAM: A what?

356
00:14:37,841 --> 00:14:38,881
A really good one.

357
00:14:39,001 --> 00:14:40,921
What? So none of this is real?

358
00:14:41,041 --> 00:14:43,841
The hotel is, and the pool.

359
00:14:43,961 --> 00:14:45,921
But you reach
a certain point...

360
00:14:46,041 --> 00:14:46,921
(KNOCKS)

361
00:14:47,041 --> 00:14:51,041
These are usually built in
cities so no-one has to travel.

362
00:14:51,161 --> 00:14:52,761
Our guests now get
off-world holiday

363
00:14:52,881 --> 00:14:53,841
for a fraction of the price.

364
00:14:53,961 --> 00:14:55,641
If they survive.

365
00:14:55,761 --> 00:14:57,521
You built this somewhere
you shouldn't,

366
00:14:57,641 --> 00:14:58,721
thinking no-one'd notice

367
00:14:58,841 --> 00:15:01,361
if you could only get
in and out by teleport.

368
00:15:01,481 --> 00:15:03,441
I heard your little chat
about 02 levels.

369
00:15:03,561 --> 00:15:04,881
That's a completely
different environment

370
00:15:05,001 --> 00:15:06,321
out there. The native species

371
00:15:06,441 --> 00:15:08,281
want you and your guests dead.

372
00:15:08,401 --> 00:15:10,801
Doctor, you need to see this!

373
00:15:10,921 --> 00:15:12,921
They've built a wall
all around this hotel.

374
00:15:13,041 --> 00:15:15,361
Vilma said it's the first
off-world fake-cation.

375
00:15:15,481 --> 00:15:18,441
Done that bit. Feel the lump
on my bonce. Do that.

376
00:15:18,561 --> 00:15:21,081
- What?
- But my Benni is missing.

377
00:15:21,201 --> 00:15:23,201
According to this,
he's outside the shields.

378
00:15:23,321 --> 00:15:25,841
You can't just walk outside.
There's not enough oxygen.

379
00:15:25,961 --> 00:15:27,121
He'd be dead
before we reach him.

380
00:15:27,241 --> 00:15:29,641
He has an oxygen tank.

381
00:15:29,761 --> 00:15:32,081
We have to find him.

382
00:15:32,201 --> 00:15:33,361
He came here because of you.

383
00:15:34,881 --> 00:15:36,841
If there's even the slightest
chance of finding him,

384
00:15:36,961 --> 00:15:38,601
you need to do it. We'll help.

385
00:15:38,721 --> 00:15:41,721
Get transport. I'll gather
everyone in the bar.

386
00:15:44,761 --> 00:15:46,081
Now, Kane!

387
00:15:52,241 --> 00:15:55,761
You get one 02 canister each.
Conserve it.

388
00:15:55,881 --> 00:15:58,481
Green is good, orange is bad,
red's dead.

389
00:15:58,601 --> 00:15:59,761
Oh...

390
00:15:59,881 --> 00:16:01,521
The good news -
these are smart.

391
00:16:01,641 --> 00:16:03,761
Tn an 02-rich environment,
They refill themselves.

392
00:16:03,881 --> 00:16:05,801
Outside this dome,
he only 02-rich environment

393
00:16:05,921 --> 00:16:08,001
on the planet
will be inside the truck.

394
00:16:08,121 --> 00:16:10,401
Do not exit
without my permission.

395
00:16:10,521 --> 00:16:12,521
Keep an eye on your readings.

396
00:16:12,641 --> 00:16:15,481
They'll change colour if you
are running low on oxygen.

397
00:16:15,601 --> 00:16:19,801
Nevi, cockle, my nose thingy
and this breathing apparatus,

398
00:16:19,921 --> 00:16:20,841
is it on right?

399
00:16:20,961 --> 00:16:21,921
Yeah, it's fine.

400
00:16:22,041 --> 00:16:23,481
Dad, it-it's not right.

401
00:16:23,601 --> 00:16:24,681
(BEEPING)

402
00:16:24,801 --> 00:16:26,201
We'd better go
and fire up the truck.

403
00:16:26,321 --> 00:16:27,961
- SYLAS: Yeah.
- I built it myself.

404
00:16:28,081 --> 00:16:29,041
Good.

405
00:16:29,161 --> 00:16:31,281
Tell me
you helped him build it.

406
00:16:31,401 --> 00:16:32,561
KANE: We're moving out!

407
00:16:34,921 --> 00:16:36,201
You owe me some answers.

408
00:16:36,321 --> 00:16:37,521
This is my operation.

409
00:16:37,641 --> 00:16:39,521
Well, it's clearly going well.
What planet is this?

410
00:16:39,641 --> 00:16:40,921
Orphan 55.

411
00:16:41,041 --> 00:16:43,881
You built a fake-cation on
an orphan planet? Are you mad?

412
00:16:44,001 --> 00:16:46,401
The radiation's dropped.
It's safe in short spells.

413
00:16:46,521 --> 00:16:47,961
Get in the truck.

414
00:16:51,721 --> 00:16:54,481
Always remain
inside the vehicle.

415
00:16:54,601 --> 00:16:58,001
This vehicle is the property
of Tranquillity Spa,

416
00:16:58,121 --> 00:16:59,881
your home from home.

417
00:17:04,121 --> 00:17:05,601
RYAN: Was we inside that?

418
00:17:05,721 --> 00:17:07,321
YAZ: This whole planet
looks dead.

419
00:17:07,441 --> 00:17:10,401
It is. It's an orphan planet.

420
00:17:10,521 --> 00:17:13,441
It's a grading that means
it's become too toxic for life.

421
00:17:13,561 --> 00:17:14,681
We're not safe out here.

422
00:17:14,801 --> 00:17:17,761
GRAHAM: Well, we weren't
exactly safe in there.

423
00:17:23,481 --> 00:17:26,721
Come on, Doc, explain. Why
is it called an orphan planet?

424
00:17:26,841 --> 00:17:29,001
DOCTOR: Because it's
uninhabitable. In societies

425
00:17:29,121 --> 00:17:31,641
that let this happen, there's
nearly always a ruling elite

426
00:17:31,761 --> 00:17:34,601
that gets to evacuate, and then
signs off all responsibility

427
00:17:34,721 --> 00:17:36,361
for whatever
they've left behind.

428
00:17:36,481 --> 00:17:37,441
That's messed up.

429
00:17:37,561 --> 00:17:39,001
Happens more than you think.

430
00:17:39,121 --> 00:17:40,921
This is Orphan 55.

431
00:17:41,041 --> 00:17:42,561
And if you can't evacuate?

432
00:17:42,681 --> 00:17:46,361
You die.
All sentient life dies.

433
00:17:46,481 --> 00:17:47,881
That's how it gets the grading.

434
00:17:48,001 --> 00:17:50,881
Except on Orphan 55,
something clearly survived.

435
00:17:51,001 --> 00:17:52,121
RYAN: The Dregs.

436
00:17:52,241 --> 00:17:55,041
Why here, Kane?
Why build this hotel?

437
00:17:55,161 --> 00:17:56,521
It doesn't make any sense.

438
00:17:56,641 --> 00:17:57,721
The air's unbreathable,

439
00:17:57,841 --> 00:17:59,561
but a few years
with the right terraforming,

440
00:17:59,681 --> 00:18:01,681
we can reduce the CO2 and make
the whole planet habitable.

441
00:18:01,801 --> 00:18:04,801
Terraforming
bankrolled by fake-cation.

442
00:18:04,921 --> 00:18:06,121
Smart.

443
00:18:06,241 --> 00:18:07,681
Today hotelier, tomorrow...

444
00:18:07,801 --> 00:18:10,401
...the proud owner
of Orphan 55,

445
00:18:10,521 --> 00:18:12,641
the best real estate
in the galaxy.

446
00:18:12,761 --> 00:18:15,081
If you can sort out your
Dreg problem, you'll be rich.

447
00:18:15,201 --> 00:18:16,841
(TRACKER BEEPS)

448
00:18:16,961 --> 00:18:19,801
Hey, Doc.
Benni's changed direction.

449
00:18:19,921 --> 00:18:22,441
VILMA: Why would he do that?

450
00:18:25,321 --> 00:18:27,681
Maybe he's heading back
to the dome.

451
00:18:29,401 --> 00:18:31,641
- Abort the mission.
- (BRAKES SCREECH)

452
00:18:31,761 --> 00:18:33,321
He's alive!
We know where he is!

453
00:18:33,441 --> 00:18:36,321
He's moving at
37 clicks an hour.

454
00:18:36,441 --> 00:18:38,281
That doesn't
sound like my Benni.

455
00:18:38,401 --> 00:18:40,121
The Dregs got him. We abort.

456
00:18:40,241 --> 00:18:45,281
If those things have got Benni,
we're getting him back!

457
00:18:45,401 --> 00:18:48,361
You want money, Kane?
That's worth a fortune!

458
00:18:48,481 --> 00:18:49,881
BELLA: That would buy
a lot of terraforming.

459
00:18:50,001 --> 00:18:52,681
Or don't you want to be Queen
of Orphan 55 any more, Kane?

460
00:18:52,801 --> 00:18:55,721
DOCTOR: Never mind the money,
there's a man's life at stake.

461
00:19:02,001 --> 00:19:03,761
Vorm, follow the tracker.

462
00:19:03,881 --> 00:19:05,361
- (VEHICLE STARTS)
- Oh...

463
00:19:09,001 --> 00:19:12,401
External oxygen levels 2%.

464
00:19:12,521 --> 00:19:16,001
Current internal
oxygen levels 27 %.

465
00:19:16,121 --> 00:19:17,361
Always remain in...

466
00:19:17,481 --> 00:19:19,681
So what do you actually
know about the Dregs?

467
00:19:19,801 --> 00:19:21,361
How many are there?

468
00:19:21,481 --> 00:19:23,401
...Is the property
of Tranquillity Spa.

469
00:19:24,841 --> 00:19:26,961
Don't want to talk to me? Fine.

470
00:19:27,081 --> 00:19:28,441
I don't need a second person
for a conversation.

471
00:19:28,561 --> 00:19:31,161
A lot of the time
they just get in the way. So...

472
00:19:31,281 --> 00:19:34,481
A Dreg is a native species
that somehow lived

473
00:19:34,601 --> 00:19:36,441
through the fallout.

474
00:19:36,561 --> 00:19:39,321
That's generations.
There must be a few of them.

475
00:19:39,441 --> 00:19:41,961
Hyph3n with a 3,
your face tells me I'm right.

476
00:19:42,081 --> 00:19:43,761
But how did they survive?

477
00:19:45,161 --> 00:19:48,601
And why is your gun fitted
with an exciplex modulator?

478
00:19:48,721 --> 00:19:50,681
They randomise laser output.

479
00:19:52,041 --> 00:19:53,761
You'd only need that
against a thing

480
00:19:53,881 --> 00:19:55,561
that could adapt
to your attack.

481
00:19:57,321 --> 00:19:58,681
Hang on.

482
00:20:00,441 --> 00:20:02,041
That's what they do?

483
00:20:02,161 --> 00:20:03,561
Adapt?

484
00:20:03,681 --> 00:20:06,441
To guns and to nuclear winter?!

485
00:20:06,561 --> 00:20:09,121
Apex predators! And we...
We are driving

486
00:20:09,241 --> 00:20:11,081
straight into their territory!

487
00:20:11,401 --> 00:20:13,241
(WIND HOWLS)

488
00:20:15,041 --> 00:20:18,361
(SNARLS)

489
00:20:18,481 --> 00:20:20,681
(ALL SNARL)

490
00:20:32,081 --> 00:20:33,601
So, er...

491
00:20:36,681 --> 00:20:39,241
...how long
have you been unemployed?

492
00:20:40,521 --> 00:20:42,761
Is that the worst chat-up line
ever?

493
00:20:44,481 --> 00:20:45,921
Yeah.

494
00:20:46,041 --> 00:20:47,761
You just witnessed history.

495
00:20:53,721 --> 00:20:56,601
I've been unemployed
for a month.

496
00:20:56,721 --> 00:20:59,681
I was my dad's carer,
but...he died.

497
00:21:00,841 --> 00:21:02,721
Oh. Sorry.

498
00:21:04,241 --> 00:21:06,321
I lost my mum eight years back.

499
00:21:07,641 --> 00:21:10,761
Have you got anyone else?
Is your mum around?

500
00:21:10,881 --> 00:21:13,561
She died
when I was about Sylas's age.

501
00:21:13,681 --> 00:21:15,921
She made Nevi look like
Parent of the Year.

502
00:21:17,441 --> 00:21:20,121
So...guys...

503
00:21:20,241 --> 00:21:22,121
...what's going on?

504
00:21:24,161 --> 00:21:25,761
Just talking.

505
00:21:25,881 --> 00:21:27,721
- Having a conversation.
- Great.

506
00:21:27,841 --> 00:21:29,801
Where are we up to?

507
00:21:29,921 --> 00:21:33,481
Yeah, Ryan.
What are you talking about?

508
00:21:35,041 --> 00:21:38,441
Er, er, we both have
dead parents.

509
00:21:38,561 --> 00:21:39,961
(BANG!)

510
00:21:40,081 --> 00:21:42,681
This vehicle is experiencing
momentary difficulties.

511
00:21:42,801 --> 00:21:46,561
This vehicle is experiencing
momentary difficulties.

512
00:21:49,121 --> 00:21:51,201
(CRACKLING) 7his vehicle
ls compromised.

513
00:21:51,321 --> 00:21:53,241
What the hell was that?

514
00:21:53,361 --> 00:21:56,641
This vehicle is compromised.

515
00:21:56,761 --> 00:22:00,161
Please stay inside the vehicle
and wait for assistance.

516
00:22:00,281 --> 00:22:02,441
DOCTOR: This is a trap,
presumably set by the Dregs.

517
00:22:02,561 --> 00:22:04,241
This mist is highly toxic,

518
00:22:04,361 --> 00:22:06,401
and when it clears,
direct sunlight is worse.

519
00:22:06,521 --> 00:22:09,281
We get ten minutes
of solar blistering and then...

520
00:22:09,401 --> 00:22:10,681
...death.

521
00:22:12,361 --> 00:22:14,201
Solar blistering?
What a lovely phrase.

522
00:22:14,321 --> 00:22:15,281
Here's another one.

523
00:22:15,401 --> 00:22:17,921
Completely knackered vehicle.
We're stranded.

524
00:22:18,041 --> 00:22:19,561
KANE: I need to check
where we are.

525
00:22:19,681 --> 00:22:22,841
(GROWLING)

526
00:22:22,961 --> 00:22:25,001
KANE: There's a service tunnel
close by.

527
00:22:25,121 --> 00:22:28,161
If we can make it to that,
we might live.

528
00:22:28,281 --> 00:22:30,201
OK. Bad news is,
we have to leave the truck

529
00:22:30,321 --> 00:22:31,241
and head out on foot.

530
00:22:31,361 --> 00:22:34,201
Not ideal,
but basically our only option.

531
00:22:34,321 --> 00:22:36,321
We can't leave! I paid you.

532
00:22:36,441 --> 00:22:38,201
We came here for Benni!

533
00:22:38,321 --> 00:22:39,841
Stay quiet, move fast.

534
00:22:39,961 --> 00:22:41,561
VILMA: Kane! Kane!

535
00:22:41,681 --> 00:22:42,641
RYAN: All right, let's go.

536
00:22:42,761 --> 00:22:44,401
We'll find him, Vilma,
I promise.

537
00:22:51,481 --> 00:22:54,401
KANE: Tunnel entrance
is just past this ridge.

538
00:22:58,921 --> 00:23:01,481
Benni! Benni! Where are you?

539
00:23:01,601 --> 00:23:02,801
- Shh, shh!
- Oh...

540
00:23:02,921 --> 00:23:03,961
DOCTOR: You'll bring the Dregs.

541
00:23:04,081 --> 00:23:07,081
They're massing
in the hills all around us.

542
00:23:07,201 --> 00:23:10,441
(GROWLING)

543
00:23:11,521 --> 00:23:13,081
GRAHAM:
Doc, we don't stand a chance.

544
00:23:13,201 --> 00:23:15,321
(SNARLING)

545
00:23:21,241 --> 00:23:24,121
Everyone,
back to the truck! Now!

546
00:23:24,241 --> 00:23:25,561
Go, go!

547
00:23:27,121 --> 00:23:29,921
(SNARLING)

548
00:23:31,401 --> 00:23:32,241
NEVI: So what's the plan now?

549
00:23:32,361 --> 00:23:33,881
KANE: Shut...up.

550
00:23:35,401 --> 00:23:36,601
(GROWLING)

551
00:23:46,321 --> 00:23:47,201
What are we going to do?

552
00:23:47,321 --> 00:23:49,121
KANE: Vorm, we're going
to deal with the Dregs.

553
00:23:49,241 --> 00:23:52,841
Doctor, get them out,
head east, look for a hatch.

554
00:23:52,961 --> 00:23:54,161
We'll keep them busy.

555
00:23:56,201 --> 00:23:57,641
- BENNI: Vilma.
- (GASPS)

556
00:23:57,761 --> 00:24:00,321
(GROWLING)

557
00:24:00,441 --> 00:24:01,801
BENNI: Are you in there?

558
00:24:01,921 --> 00:24:03,801
Benni?

559
00:24:03,921 --> 00:24:06,041
- Benni!
- Shh!

560
00:24:06,161 --> 00:24:08,721
- Benni!
- Shh-shh.

561
00:24:08,841 --> 00:24:09,961
GRAHAM: The Dregs have got him.

562
00:24:10,081 --> 00:24:11,521
- (GROWLING)
- YAZ: Shh-shh-shh.

563
00:24:11,641 --> 00:24:14,001
BENNI: Vilma!

564
00:24:14,121 --> 00:24:16,561
I can't believe you came!

565
00:24:16,681 --> 00:24:19,681
I'm not alone,
and I don't have long...

566
00:24:19,801 --> 00:24:21,001
(GROWLING)

567
00:24:21,121 --> 00:24:24,201
...but I-I have two questions.

568
00:24:24,321 --> 00:24:26,681
I'm sorry to ask them together.

569
00:24:28,161 --> 00:24:29,681
Will you marry me?

570
00:24:29,801 --> 00:24:33,601
Oh, of course I will!

571
00:24:33,721 --> 00:24:36,201
Yes!

572
00:24:36,321 --> 00:24:37,961
What was the other one?

573
00:24:38,081 --> 00:24:39,081
BENNTI: If anyone can,

574
00:24:39,201 --> 00:24:41,201
will they please shoot me?

575
00:24:41,321 --> 00:24:44,281
- (GROWLING)
- Oh, Benni!

576
00:24:44,401 --> 00:24:46,761
What has it done to you?

577
00:24:46,881 --> 00:24:49,561
(SNARLING)

578
00:24:49,681 --> 00:24:51,321
We've got to get out of here.

579
00:24:51,441 --> 00:24:53,961
We shouldn't
have left the dome.

580
00:24:54,081 --> 00:24:56,641
(SCREAMS)

581
00:24:56,761 --> 00:24:58,521
Vorm! This is it!

582
00:24:58,641 --> 00:25:00,281
- This is the job!
- GRAHAM: Come on!

583
00:25:03,161 --> 00:25:04,641
RYAN: Let's go!

584
00:25:04,761 --> 00:25:07,281
DOCTOR: Sylas, now! Head
to the ridge. Don't look back!

585
00:25:08,801 --> 00:25:10,241
Come on.

586
00:25:10,361 --> 00:25:11,641
(GROWLING)

587
00:25:11,761 --> 00:25:13,481
Hyph3n, hurry!

588
00:25:15,041 --> 00:25:16,041
(SNARLS)

589
00:25:16,161 --> 00:25:18,841
(SCREAMS)

590
00:25:18,961 --> 00:25:22,201
(ROARS)

591
00:25:24,041 --> 00:25:25,801
Come on, come on.

592
00:25:25,921 --> 00:25:28,801
- DOCTOR: Kane, what happened?
- It threw me.

593
00:25:28,921 --> 00:25:30,281
- Are you OK?
- They've got Vorm!

594
00:25:30,401 --> 00:25:31,881
(SNARLING AND SCREAMING)

595
00:25:32,001 --> 00:25:33,721
Get me back up there!

596
00:25:33,841 --> 00:25:35,481
You can't fight any more.

597
00:25:35,601 --> 00:25:36,721
Vorm needs me.

598
00:25:36,841 --> 00:25:39,641
We need you. You know this
planet. Get us to the tunnels.

599
00:25:39,761 --> 00:25:41,681
(SNARLING)

600
00:26:06,721 --> 00:26:08,841
GRAHAM: How can it be
even hotter down here?

601
00:26:08,961 --> 00:26:10,321
DOCTOR: Oxygen check.

602
00:26:10,441 --> 00:26:12,281
Dad, we're doing oxygen checks.

603
00:26:12,401 --> 00:26:14,521
As green as the hair
on our heads, Sylas.

604
00:26:14,641 --> 00:26:15,641
KANE: We're safe.

605
00:26:15,761 --> 00:26:17,361
There's a short-range
maintenance teleport here,

606
00:26:17,481 --> 00:26:19,161
which should just get us
back to base.

607
00:26:19,281 --> 00:26:21,481
Stay close. There's only
enough power for one use.

608
00:26:21,601 --> 00:26:24,841
Kane, when you were fighting
the Dreg,

609
00:26:24,961 --> 00:26:26,681
did you see Benni?

610
00:26:26,801 --> 00:26:28,001
Yeah.

611
00:26:28,121 --> 00:26:29,761
Don't worry. I killed him.

612
00:26:29,881 --> 00:26:31,001
Oh!

613
00:26:31,121 --> 00:26:33,081
GRAHAM: What did you just say?

614
00:26:33,201 --> 00:26:34,321
Benni?

615
00:26:34,441 --> 00:26:36,201
He asked me to.

616
00:26:36,321 --> 00:26:38,041
Oh!

617
00:26:38,161 --> 00:26:41,361
How...? How could you?!

618
00:26:41,481 --> 00:26:43,721
Come on. Come on, Vilma.
I got you.

619
00:26:43,841 --> 00:26:45,921
What is wrong with you?

620
00:26:46,041 --> 00:26:47,721
Why didn't the Dreg kill him?

621
00:26:47,841 --> 00:26:49,001
He was having fun.

622
00:26:49,121 --> 00:26:50,961
There's a room down there
where I stashed a medipack.

623
00:26:51,081 --> 00:26:53,561
Fetch it
and we can get out of here.

624
00:26:53,681 --> 00:26:54,841
You're not getting
out of anywhere.

625
00:26:54,961 --> 00:26:56,481
Bella!

626
00:26:56,601 --> 00:27:00,521
- What are you doing?
- Shut up! I will shoot you.

627
00:27:02,521 --> 00:27:04,361
Where's the maintenance
teleport, Kane?

628
00:27:04,481 --> 00:27:05,921
I'd rather die than tell you.

629
00:27:06,041 --> 00:27:07,361
Oh, you're going to die.

630
00:27:07,481 --> 00:27:09,281
It's just whether
I shoot and kill you now

631
00:27:09,401 --> 00:27:10,921
or wound you
and leave you to the Dregs.

632
00:27:11,041 --> 00:27:12,241
What is it you want?

633
00:27:12,361 --> 00:27:15,001
To burn everything
you've built to the ground.

634
00:27:15,121 --> 00:27:16,401
Who are you?

635
00:27:17,601 --> 00:27:18,841
Me?

636
00:27:18,961 --> 00:27:20,121
I'm no-one.

637
00:27:20,241 --> 00:27:21,681
I was my dad's carer.

638
00:27:22,801 --> 00:27:26,441
Bella...why are you
doing this?

639
00:27:26,561 --> 00:27:29,201
My mum didn't really die.

640
00:27:29,321 --> 00:27:32,161
She just never came
to any of my birthdays.

641
00:27:32,281 --> 00:27:34,321
She didn't come to his funeral.

642
00:27:34,441 --> 00:27:37,161
And she doesn't even
recognise me now.

643
00:27:39,041 --> 00:27:41,201
Trixabelle...

644
00:27:41,321 --> 00:27:43,921
Oh! And she gave me
the name Trixabelle.

645
00:27:46,441 --> 00:27:48,481
The teleport's behind you.

646
00:27:51,241 --> 00:27:52,081
DOCTOR: Oh!

647
00:27:52,201 --> 00:27:54,281
Come on!

648
00:27:55,601 --> 00:27:57,761
This is not the way
to resolve a family dispute.

649
00:27:57,881 --> 00:28:00,961
How about good old-fashioned
passive-aggressive discussion?

650
00:28:01,081 --> 00:28:03,241
(SNARLING)

651
00:28:08,121 --> 00:28:09,921
Bella!

652
00:28:16,601 --> 00:28:18,161
Tranquillity Spa
ls experiencing...

653
00:28:18,281 --> 00:28:21,041
- I didn't ask you to do that!
- You're welcome.

654
00:28:21,161 --> 00:28:22,721
We need to find a way
to help the others get back.

655
00:28:22,841 --> 00:28:25,001
No. They can sort
themselves out.

656
00:28:25,121 --> 00:28:27,721
Hey, hey, hey.
These people are my family.

657
00:28:27,841 --> 00:28:30,081
We're finding a way.

658
00:28:30,201 --> 00:28:33,801
Too late. I'm here
to burn this place down,

659
00:28:33,921 --> 00:28:37,081
and if you're not with me,
you'll die here too.

660
00:28:37,201 --> 00:28:39,601
Our staff are aware. Relax.

661
00:28:42,201 --> 00:28:44,441
- Hang on, where's Ryan?
- With Bella.

662
00:28:44,561 --> 00:28:46,281
Hopefully,
the maintenance teleport

663
00:28:46,401 --> 00:28:47,401
has got them back to the hotel.

664
00:28:47,521 --> 00:28:50,601
OK, listen up.
There's stairs just beyond here

665
00:28:50,721 --> 00:28:52,401
that will take us down
and back.

666
00:28:52,521 --> 00:28:54,201
Just one catch - the route
goes through a Dreg nest.

667
00:28:54,321 --> 00:28:56,801
That's madness!
We'll never make it through!

668
00:28:56,921 --> 00:28:59,681
(SNARLING)

669
00:28:59,801 --> 00:29:00,761
Oxygen supply falling.

670
00:29:00,881 --> 00:29:03,961
You talk too much.
Using up all your oxygen.

671
00:29:04,081 --> 00:29:06,481
Consider urgently
refilling this canister.

672
00:29:06,601 --> 00:29:08,961
(SNARLING)

673
00:29:09,081 --> 00:29:12,161
Consider urgently
refilling this canister.

674
00:29:14,281 --> 00:29:17,241
That daughter of yours, Kane -
real chip off the old block.

675
00:29:17,361 --> 00:29:19,201
I didn't know she was here.

676
00:29:20,561 --> 00:29:23,601
So you left her and her dad
and never got back in contact?

677
00:29:23,721 --> 00:29:25,841
You don't get to judge me.

678
00:29:25,961 --> 00:29:28,521
This project, Tranquillity Spa,

679
00:29:28,641 --> 00:29:31,201
I was only doing it
to give to her.

680
00:29:32,601 --> 00:29:34,321
YAZ: Maybe you should
have mentioned that

681
00:29:34,441 --> 00:29:35,721
before you pulled a gun on her.

682
00:29:37,961 --> 00:29:40,441
RYAN: OK, we're not really
going to burn this place down,

683
00:29:40,561 --> 00:29:42,481
- are we?
- Nope.

684
00:29:42,601 --> 00:29:44,361
We're blowing it up.

685
00:29:47,161 --> 00:29:48,161
What?

686
00:29:49,361 --> 00:29:51,401
You...built a bomb?

687
00:29:51,521 --> 00:29:54,401
(SCOFFS) Oh, I've built
more than one.

688
00:30:02,601 --> 00:30:03,521
Reminder.

689
00:30:03,641 --> 00:30:06,361
Please locate breathable air
in order to recharge supply.

690
00:30:06,481 --> 00:30:09,321
Oh, I'm sorry.
I'm slowing you down.

691
00:30:09,441 --> 00:30:11,001
No, don't worry, don't worry.

692
00:30:11,121 --> 00:30:12,841
(BEEPING)

693
00:30:12,961 --> 00:30:15,321
We're using too much oxygen.

694
00:30:15,441 --> 00:30:18,281
(GROWLING)

695
00:30:18,401 --> 00:30:20,761
KANE: That's more of them.
They know where we are.

696
00:30:20,881 --> 00:30:22,801
They'll be too fast for us.
Take cover.

697
00:30:22,921 --> 00:30:24,721
I'll try and get a shot.

698
00:30:27,401 --> 00:30:29,921
- YAZ: What is it?
- DOCTOR: Nothing. Keep moving.

699
00:30:30,041 --> 00:30:31,201
GRAHAM: Hey,
what are you doing?

700
00:30:31,321 --> 00:30:33,841
- I said it's nothing!
- No, let us see!

701
00:30:40,281 --> 00:30:41,401
That looks like Russian.

702
00:30:44,601 --> 00:30:45,761
Novosibirsk.

703
00:30:46,881 --> 00:30:49,041
It's a Siberian
underground station.

704
00:30:51,361 --> 00:30:52,761
This is Earth.

705
00:30:58,161 --> 00:31:01,441
No, no, no. It can't be Earth.
This is nothing like Earth.

706
00:31:04,241 --> 00:31:06,201
(GROWLING)

707
00:31:08,521 --> 00:31:10,561
- DOCTOR: Hide. Hide!
- GRAHAM: Come on!

708
00:31:12,241 --> 00:31:13,441
KANE: Get down.
I've got a shot.

709
00:31:13,561 --> 00:31:14,561
DOCTOR: There's too many
of them!

710
00:31:14,681 --> 00:31:16,681
You don't have
enough ammunition!

711
00:31:16,801 --> 00:31:19,401
- We have to run for it.
- Vilma can't run.

712
00:31:19,521 --> 00:31:20,681
(GROWLING)

713
00:31:20,801 --> 00:31:25,281
Yaz, promise me...you'll run.

714
00:31:25,401 --> 00:31:26,681
You can't hide by yourself.

715
00:31:26,801 --> 00:31:28,921
Run.

716
00:31:29,041 --> 00:31:30,161
Stay alive.

717
00:31:30,281 --> 00:31:31,361
(GROWLING)

718
00:31:31,481 --> 00:31:33,921
- Vilma!
- Hey!

719
00:31:34,041 --> 00:31:35,681
- (SNARLING)
- Over here!

720
00:31:35,801 --> 00:31:39,841
Which one of you
hurt my Benni?!

721
00:31:39,961 --> 00:31:43,281
(SNARLING AND SCREAMING)

722
00:31:43,401 --> 00:31:44,961
Don't tell me
that's another hopper virus.

723
00:31:45,081 --> 00:31:46,601
Yep. And this time
I'll put it somewhere

724
00:31:46,721 --> 00:31:48,441
the Doctor won't be able
to isolate...

725
00:31:50,281 --> 00:31:51,761
You said you were with me!

726
00:31:51,881 --> 00:31:53,241
You can't blow this place up!

727
00:31:53,361 --> 00:31:55,721
I've spent my whole life
wondering about her,

728
00:31:55,841 --> 00:31:58,321
and she's never thought once
about me!

729
00:31:59,641 --> 00:32:01,201
I will shoot you.

730
00:32:01,321 --> 00:32:02,641
Tranquillity Spa
ls experiencing

731
00:32:02,761 --> 00:32:04,961
momentary
operational difficulties.

732
00:32:05,081 --> 00:32:06,721
Go on, then.

733
00:32:06,841 --> 00:32:09,081
(BANG!)

734
00:32:09,201 --> 00:32:11,441
There was a smaller bomb
in the bar too.

735
00:32:11,561 --> 00:32:13,441
I wasn't going to use it
when anyone was here!

736
00:32:13,561 --> 00:32:14,961
(ALARM BEEPS)

737
00:32:15,081 --> 00:32:17,041
But it just blew up
the mainframe.

738
00:32:21,561 --> 00:32:24,161
KANE: This is a nest.
Watch out for dormant Dregs.

739
00:32:24,281 --> 00:32:25,521
They sleep standing up.

740
00:32:25,641 --> 00:32:27,961
The stairs are the other side.
We need to go through.

741
00:32:28,081 --> 00:32:29,441
Silently.

742
00:32:34,841 --> 00:32:37,161
We should have been able
to help her.

743
00:32:37,281 --> 00:32:41,401
She died, bless her, so we can
get out of here. Come on.

744
00:32:41,521 --> 00:32:43,321
- Tell us what you know.
- (BEEPING)

745
00:32:43,441 --> 00:32:47,121
How can this be possible?
How did the Dregs get here?

746
00:32:47,241 --> 00:32:48,721
When did the planet
get invaded?

747
00:32:48,841 --> 00:32:51,081
Oxygen supply level 1%.

748
00:32:51,201 --> 00:32:53,521
You must find breathable air
immediately.

749
00:32:53,641 --> 00:32:56,441
Oxygen supply level 1%.

750
00:32:56,561 --> 00:32:58,601
Immediate action required.

751
00:32:58,721 --> 00:33:00,921
Refill oxygen canister.

752
00:33:01,041 --> 00:33:02,881
Find breathable air.

753
00:33:03,001 --> 00:33:05,601
Failure to do so
will result in threat to life.

754
00:33:13,681 --> 00:33:16,281
NEVI: These stairs should
take us back to Tranquillity.

755
00:33:19,481 --> 00:33:21,321
GRAHAM: Wait, where's the Doc?

756
00:33:21,441 --> 00:33:23,321
Oxygen supply level 1%.

757
00:33:23,441 --> 00:33:26,401
You must find breathable air
immediately.

758
00:33:26,521 --> 00:33:28,721
Oxygen supply level 1%.

759
00:33:28,841 --> 00:33:30,921
- Immediate action is required.
- Oh, do shut up.

760
00:33:31,041 --> 00:33:33,361
- Refill oxygen canister.
- (GASPS FOR BREATH)

761
00:33:33,481 --> 00:33:35,121
Find breathable air.

762
00:33:35,241 --> 00:33:38,121
Failure to do so will result
in threat to life.

763
00:33:38,241 --> 00:33:39,641
(DREG SNORES)

764
00:33:46,041 --> 00:33:48,001
(INHALES)

765
00:33:49,881 --> 00:33:51,761
(BEEPING)

766
00:33:51,881 --> 00:33:54,201
Oxygen supply refilling.

767
00:33:54,321 --> 00:33:56,521
Oxygen supply refilling.

768
00:33:56,641 --> 00:33:59,161
Well, aren't you
full of surprises?

769
00:33:59,281 --> 00:34:01,521
I need to understand
one more thing now.

770
00:34:02,561 --> 00:34:04,601
Checking what's in here.

771
00:34:10,881 --> 00:34:11,881
(GASPS)

772
00:34:13,081 --> 00:34:15,321
That's what I was afraid of.

773
00:34:16,881 --> 00:34:17,761
(SNARLS)

774
00:34:17,881 --> 00:34:19,761
(SCREAMS)

775
00:34:22,241 --> 00:34:23,801
KANE: Doctor!

776
00:34:25,241 --> 00:34:27,441
(ROARS)

777
00:34:27,561 --> 00:34:28,881
Over here!

778
00:34:29,001 --> 00:34:32,121
It's so strong without oxygen
because it doesn't need it.

779
00:34:32,241 --> 00:34:34,921
It breathes carbon dioxide in
and oxygen out,

780
00:34:35,041 --> 00:34:37,001
like a really angry tree!

781
00:34:37,121 --> 00:34:39,321
Thank you, but you should
not have come back for me.

782
00:34:39,441 --> 00:34:40,641
I didn't.

783
00:34:40,761 --> 00:34:42,521
But I can buy you some time.

784
00:34:42,641 --> 00:34:44,681
- No. You owe her!
- I owe you all.

785
00:34:44,801 --> 00:34:46,401
For starting this.

786
00:34:46,521 --> 00:34:47,761
Tell her I'm sorry.

787
00:34:49,001 --> 00:34:49,921
She deserved better.

788
00:34:50,041 --> 00:34:51,801
- (YELLS)
- (GUNFIRE)

789
00:34:51,921 --> 00:34:53,321
Kane!

790
00:34:54,441 --> 00:34:56,441
This is an emergency
announcement...

791
00:34:56,561 --> 00:34:58,081
GRAHAM: Whoa, what happened
in here?

792
00:34:58,201 --> 00:34:59,281
YAZ: I'm guessing Bella.

793
00:34:59,401 --> 00:35:00,521
NEVI: If they think
I'm clearing all this up...

794
00:35:00,641 --> 00:35:02,921
(GASPS FOR BREATH)

795
00:35:03,041 --> 00:35:04,441
This is an emergency
announcement.

796
00:35:04,561 --> 00:35:08,361
Come on. We need to close
this up. Secure the room.

797
00:35:08,481 --> 00:35:09,641
Come on, give us a hand.

798
00:35:09,761 --> 00:35:12,081
One, two, three!

799
00:35:12,201 --> 00:35:13,241
(GROWLING)

800
00:35:13,361 --> 00:35:14,721
NEVI: We need to block
this off.

801
00:35:14,841 --> 00:35:16,081
The vending machine! Come on.

802
00:35:16,201 --> 00:35:17,481
- NEVI: Good idea.
- SYLAS: Quick!

803
00:35:17,601 --> 00:35:18,921
(YELLS)

804
00:35:19,041 --> 00:35:20,401
GRAHAM: Drop it, drop it!
Come on, that's it.

805
00:35:20,521 --> 00:35:23,321
- (SNARLING)
- Let's go, let's go!

806
00:35:23,441 --> 00:35:24,641
- Hey! Doctor!
- Ryan! '

807
00:35:24,761 --> 00:35:27,961
Bella, Sylas, Nevi,
to the command centre now.

808
00:35:28,081 --> 00:35:30,361
We'll hold this off for as long
as we can - somehow.

809
00:35:30,481 --> 00:35:31,561
(SNARLING)

810
00:35:31,681 --> 00:35:33,121
"Made in China."

811
00:35:33,241 --> 00:35:34,641
Hey, how did this get here?

812
00:35:34,761 --> 00:35:36,121
It never left.

813
00:35:36,241 --> 00:35:39,121
Orphan 55 - it's Earth.
Your future.

814
00:35:39,241 --> 00:35:41,281
(SNARLING)

815
00:35:41,401 --> 00:35:43,281
If this is Earth,
then what are the Dregs?

816
00:35:43,401 --> 00:35:45,961
They're us. Mutated.

817
00:35:46,081 --> 00:35:48,281
Yes. The few that didn't die.

818
00:35:48,401 --> 00:35:49,681
Oh, no, they can't be.

819
00:35:49,801 --> 00:35:51,281
How did Earth end up like this?

820
00:35:51,401 --> 00:35:53,241
You had warnings
from every scientist alive.

821
00:35:53,361 --> 00:35:55,001
- Global warming.
- Huh?

822
00:35:55,121 --> 00:35:58,801
The food chain collapses.
Mass migration. And war.

823
00:35:58,921 --> 00:35:59,761
(ROARING)

824
00:35:59,881 --> 00:36:01,241
I can't hold this much longer.

825
00:36:01,361 --> 00:36:02,761
We need to get out of here.

826
00:36:02,881 --> 00:36:04,561
When I say run...run.

827
00:36:04,681 --> 00:36:06,481
Run!

828
00:36:06,601 --> 00:36:08,521
(ROARING)

829
00:36:10,401 --> 00:36:13,201
(ROARS)

830
00:36:14,681 --> 00:36:17,761
(ALL ROAR)

831
00:36:31,641 --> 00:36:34,201
DOCTOR: Nevi, secure that door!

832
00:36:34,321 --> 00:36:35,921
I'm trying! The autolocks
are playing up.

833
00:36:36,041 --> 00:36:38,161
(ALARM BEEPS)

834
00:36:38,281 --> 00:36:39,881
Wait, where's Kane?

835
00:36:40,841 --> 00:36:42,921
She didn't make it back.

836
00:36:44,401 --> 00:36:46,241
SYLAS: Dad,
you're doing it wrong.

837
00:36:46,361 --> 00:36:47,881
It needs a passkey
to close it from the inside.

838
00:36:48,001 --> 00:36:51,321
Not now, Sylas, OK?
I'm trying to concentrate.

839
00:36:51,441 --> 00:36:53,841
You never listen to me!
Do it yourself, then!

840
00:36:53,961 --> 00:36:57,161
Doctor, look! Outside the dome.

841
00:36:58,841 --> 00:37:01,761
DOCTOR:
Dregs responding to the call.

842
00:37:01,881 --> 00:37:02,881
They're massing for an attack.

843
00:37:03,001 --> 00:37:05,361
And the ionic membrane's down,
so they can all get in.

844
00:37:05,481 --> 00:37:06,521
We need to evacuate.

845
00:37:06,641 --> 00:37:08,801
We are on phantom power
and the teleport is dead,

846
00:37:08,921 --> 00:37:10,601
but it still knows where
each one of us came from.

847
00:37:10,721 --> 00:37:12,601
Nevi, you need to fix
the teleport.

848
00:37:12,721 --> 00:37:13,641
No way, no, I'm...

849
00:37:13,761 --> 00:37:15,761
You're the only one who knows
how to fix that thing.

850
00:37:15,881 --> 00:37:16,841
And if it doesn't work,

851
00:37:16,961 --> 00:37:18,641
we're all going to be stuck
on this planet.

852
00:37:18,761 --> 00:37:20,481
The bounce capacitor
is completely blown

853
00:37:20,601 --> 00:37:23,241
and the only fuel
we've got left is syrillium 3,

854
00:37:23,361 --> 00:37:25,481
which isn't enough to get us
off-planet.

855
00:37:25,601 --> 00:37:27,961
For that we need syrillium 4.

856
00:37:28,081 --> 00:37:32,041
Which is what...syrillium 3
mutates into

857
00:37:32,161 --> 00:37:34,601
when it's attacked
by the hopper virus.

858
00:37:34,721 --> 00:37:37,761
- Good luck with that, Dad!
- Autolocking linen cupboard.

859
00:37:37,881 --> 00:37:39,161
(BANGS SHUT)

860
00:37:39,281 --> 00:37:40,241
(GROWLING)

861
00:37:40,361 --> 00:37:41,961
NEVI: Open the door!

862
00:37:42,081 --> 00:37:44,601
Sylas is out there!
I can't get the autolocks open!

863
00:37:44,721 --> 00:37:45,641
Where is he?!

864
00:37:45,761 --> 00:37:47,681
DOCTOR: He's not in
the corridor. He must have run.

865
00:37:47,801 --> 00:37:48,961
We're all going to die here.

866
00:37:49,081 --> 00:37:51,681
Not if I've got anything
to do with it.

867
00:37:51,801 --> 00:37:53,521
I know how we can survive this.

868
00:37:53,641 --> 00:37:55,641
We have one advantage
over them.

869
00:37:55,761 --> 00:37:58,041
Oxygen. We love it.
The Dregs hate it.

870
00:37:58,161 --> 00:38:00,201
This whole dome
is air-conditioned.

871
00:38:00,321 --> 00:38:03,401
If I can up the oxygen levels,
the Dregs will be weakened

872
00:38:03,521 --> 00:38:05,121
and we'll get out of here.
Now, Nevi...

873
00:38:05,241 --> 00:38:06,521
...get on it.

874
00:38:06,641 --> 00:38:09,121
Yaz, Ryan,
the Dregs are going to attack

875
00:38:09,241 --> 00:38:11,881
the one place where
the dome wall meets the hotel.

876
00:38:12,001 --> 00:38:13,081
The steam room.

877
00:38:13,201 --> 00:38:15,641
Keep them at bay and buy us
as much time as you can.

878
00:38:15,761 --> 00:38:16,681
Graham, you're with Nevi.

879
00:38:16,801 --> 00:38:18,041
Bella, we're going
to find Sylas.

880
00:38:18,161 --> 00:38:20,201
I'll try and boost
the oxygen levels.

881
00:38:20,321 --> 00:38:22,201
BELLA: Why should I take
orders from you?

882
00:38:23,521 --> 00:38:24,681
You caused this mess.

883
00:38:24,801 --> 00:38:26,801
And now you're going
to help fix it.

884
00:38:26,921 --> 00:38:29,081
Everyone regroup
at the teleport.

885
00:38:29,201 --> 00:38:32,041
Now, I'm going
to blitz these autolocks.

886
00:38:35,841 --> 00:38:38,001
- NEVI: OK. While I do this...
- Yeah?

887
00:38:38,121 --> 00:38:41,161
...you open the drive core
and isolate the syrillium 3.

888
00:38:41,281 --> 00:38:44,281
Are you having a laugh, mate?
I'm... I'm a bus driver.

889
00:38:44,401 --> 00:38:45,961
YAZ: We need to find
something to barricade

890
00:38:46,081 --> 00:38:47,601
the breach in the wall,
stop the Dregs getting in!

891
00:38:47,721 --> 00:38:48,801
RYAN: Sun loungers?

892
00:38:48,921 --> 00:38:50,721
YAZ: Yep, sun loungers.
Last line of defence.

893
00:38:55,361 --> 00:38:57,721
Sylas must be here somewhere.

894
00:38:57,841 --> 00:38:59,481
(FAINT GROWLING)

895
00:39:00,761 --> 00:39:02,921
(GROWLING)

896
00:39:03,041 --> 00:39:04,721
DOCTOR: Ha! Found him!

897
00:39:04,841 --> 00:39:07,121
One small problem...

898
00:39:07,241 --> 00:39:08,761
You've got a plan, right?

899
00:39:08,881 --> 00:39:10,521
Oh, it's brewing.

900
00:39:10,641 --> 00:39:13,681
At least three-eighths
of a plan right here.

901
00:39:13,801 --> 00:39:15,201
Two-eighths.

902
00:39:15,321 --> 00:39:17,121
I'll be honest,
all I've got is the letter P,

903
00:39:17,241 --> 00:39:18,841
but sometimes
that's all I need.

904
00:39:18,961 --> 00:39:20,681
(GROWLING)

905
00:39:24,481 --> 00:39:26,081
(SNARLING)

906
00:39:29,601 --> 00:39:30,721
Hey, that's our oxygen supply!

907
00:39:30,841 --> 00:39:32,601
It's our only weapon!

908
00:39:32,721 --> 00:39:34,441
(SNARLS)

909
00:39:36,721 --> 00:39:39,561
DOCTOR: Got a plan.
Sylas, stay there.

910
00:39:39,681 --> 00:39:40,601
I'll distract it.

911
00:39:40,721 --> 00:39:42,441
You grab Sylas and
I'll meet you at the teleport.

912
00:39:42,561 --> 00:39:44,441
Oi! Wheezy!

913
00:39:44,561 --> 00:39:46,001
Over here!

914
00:39:46,121 --> 00:39:47,601
Yeah, I see you, Dreg leader,

915
00:39:47,721 --> 00:39:50,041
the alpha dog
of the apex predators.

916
00:39:50,161 --> 00:39:51,561
(SNARLS)

917
00:39:51,681 --> 00:39:54,041
Get to the teleport. It's OK.

918
00:39:54,161 --> 00:39:55,561
(SNARLING)

919
00:39:55,681 --> 00:39:57,801
You call,
and your species responds.

920
00:39:59,521 --> 00:40:02,801
But we need to isolate you, and
that CO2 has just shown me how.

921
00:40:02,921 --> 00:40:04,321
Right, change of plan.

922
00:40:04,441 --> 00:40:06,201
We need to keep it busy. Run!

923
00:40:07,321 --> 00:40:09,441
This way, Wheezy! Follow us!

924
00:40:09,561 --> 00:40:12,481
I can't do this!
Where's my boy?

925
00:40:12,601 --> 00:40:13,601
He'd know what to do.

926
00:40:13,721 --> 00:40:15,641
SYLAS: Whoa, that's a mess.

927
00:40:19,361 --> 00:40:22,281
Graham, move over
for a real mechanic.

928
00:40:22,401 --> 00:40:24,921
SYLAS: Gentlemen, let's make
some syrillium 4.

929
00:40:29,521 --> 00:40:31,921
There's too many of them!
There's nothing we can do!

930
00:40:32,041 --> 00:40:34,041
I've got an idea. Follow me!

931
00:40:34,161 --> 00:40:35,161
(SNARLING)

932
00:40:35,281 --> 00:40:36,721
DOCTOR: Get in the cage!

933
00:40:36,841 --> 00:40:38,841
BELLA: What are you doing?

934
00:40:38,961 --> 00:40:41,561
Isolating Wheezy.
It's the Dreg leader.

935
00:40:41,681 --> 00:40:43,361
BELLA: Then why are we
in the cage?

936
00:40:43,481 --> 00:40:45,321
Playing a hunch.

937
00:40:45,441 --> 00:40:46,601
(SNARLS)

938
00:40:46,721 --> 00:40:48,641
First we weakened it
with oxygen.

939
00:40:48,761 --> 00:40:52,041
Now we deny it the carbon
dioxide it needs to breathe.

940
00:40:52,161 --> 00:40:54,721
I know you can hear me.

941
00:40:54,841 --> 00:40:56,161
I've been in your head.

942
00:40:56,281 --> 00:40:58,801
- (SNARLS)
- This room is sealed.

943
00:40:58,921 --> 00:41:03,281
You need carbon dioxide
to convert into oxygen

944
00:41:03,401 --> 00:41:05,281
so you can breathe.

945
00:41:05,401 --> 00:41:08,441
We need oxygen
to make carbon dioxide.

946
00:41:08,561 --> 00:41:11,681
Right now we've got
a perfect ecosystem.

947
00:41:11,801 --> 00:41:14,881
Kill us, and you die too.

948
00:41:15,001 --> 00:41:17,641
Sorry. This was a trap and
you walked into it, Wheezy.

949
00:41:17,761 --> 00:41:19,721
- Step back.
- (GROWLS)

950
00:41:19,841 --> 00:41:22,041
And let us out of that door.

951
00:41:22,161 --> 00:41:24,281
It's the only way
you're gonna live.

952
00:41:24,401 --> 00:41:27,161
(ROARS)

953
00:41:27,281 --> 00:41:30,881
The people who used to have
this planet could have changed,

954
00:41:31,001 --> 00:41:32,241
but they didn't,

955
00:41:32,361 --> 00:41:34,841
so they lost everything.

956
00:41:36,201 --> 00:41:39,601
Be smarter than what made you.

957
00:41:39,721 --> 00:41:41,321
(GROWLS)

958
00:41:44,401 --> 00:41:45,881
Step away.

959
00:41:53,161 --> 00:41:54,881
Good Dreg. Smart Dreg.

960
00:41:58,121 --> 00:41:59,481
Ready?

961
00:42:06,761 --> 00:42:08,161
(GROWLS)

962
00:42:08,281 --> 00:42:11,121
The second you open that door,
it's going to kill us.

963
00:42:11,241 --> 00:42:13,481
I'm not gonna open the door
until it's in the cage.

964
00:42:13,601 --> 00:42:15,001
I'm hoping it understands that.

965
00:42:15,121 --> 00:42:17,361
(GROWLS)

966
00:42:18,801 --> 00:42:20,761
(GROWLS)

967
00:42:31,921 --> 00:42:33,761
Run. Run, run, run, run, run!

968
00:42:36,681 --> 00:42:38,881
(SNARLS)

969
00:42:39,001 --> 00:42:40,561
YAZ: You let Bella
set this bomb?

970
00:42:40,681 --> 00:42:42,961
RYAN: She had a lot of bombs
and a gun.

971
00:42:43,081 --> 00:42:44,441
I wasn't gonna argue.

972
00:42:44,561 --> 00:42:46,561
Bella's got
some serious issues.

973
00:42:46,681 --> 00:42:47,921
Yeah, lucky for us.

974
00:42:48,041 --> 00:42:49,361
(GROWLING)

975
00:42:54,441 --> 00:42:55,561
YAZ: This way.

976
00:42:59,041 --> 00:43:00,841
Add one hopper virus,
leave to simmer,

977
00:43:00,961 --> 00:43:02,681
and we'll have
our syrillium 4.

978
00:43:02,801 --> 00:43:06,121
- Well, hopefully.
- Oh, Sylas! Well played, boys.

979
00:43:06,241 --> 00:43:07,201
Please wait

980
00:43:07,321 --> 00:43:08,321
Teleport operations rebooting.

981
00:43:08,441 --> 00:43:10,881
(EXPLOSION)

982
00:43:14,881 --> 00:43:17,081
Did you both forget to mention
the massive bomb?!

983
00:43:17,201 --> 00:43:19,401
It's going to take about
a minute to get to full power.

984
00:43:19,521 --> 00:43:20,681
Nevi, we don't have a minute.

985
00:43:20,801 --> 00:43:22,201
Teleport occupancy exceeded.

986
00:43:22,321 --> 00:43:24,801
There's too many people
to transport.

987
00:43:24,921 --> 00:43:26,601
(SNARLING)

988
00:43:26,721 --> 00:43:29,161
Teleport occupancy exceeded.

989
00:43:29,281 --> 00:43:31,441
- Get out of here.
- No, Bella, come back here!

990
00:43:31,561 --> 00:43:34,481
This teleport
ls now fully operational.

991
00:43:34,601 --> 00:43:37,521
Nevi, I've set the system.
You and Sylas can go.

992
00:43:37,641 --> 00:43:40,281
Sylas, you've been brilliant.

993
00:43:40,401 --> 00:43:41,921
Bye, Doctor.

994
00:43:43,721 --> 00:43:47,321
(GROWLING)

995
00:43:49,041 --> 00:43:51,081
- Bella!
- YAZ: Weapon failed on her!

996
00:43:52,921 --> 00:43:54,401
Get away from her!

997
00:43:54,521 --> 00:43:56,401
(SNARLS)

998
00:44:04,401 --> 00:44:06,481
Got this.

999
00:44:06,601 --> 00:44:09,641
(FIRING CONTINUES)

1000
00:44:09,761 --> 00:44:13,481
O'Brien, party of four. Return
teleport profile located.

1001
00:44:13,601 --> 00:44:14,681
Teleporting.

1002
00:44:20,681 --> 00:44:22,601
We made it.

1003
00:44:25,561 --> 00:44:27,521
She... She'll be OK.

1004
00:44:27,641 --> 00:44:29,161
She'll be fine.
She's with Kane.

1005
00:44:29,281 --> 00:44:31,161
How are they going to be OK?

1006
00:44:32,441 --> 00:44:33,841
No oxygen, no help.

1007
00:44:35,561 --> 00:44:39,041
When did you know...
that it was Earth?

1008
00:44:40,721 --> 00:44:42,481
Just before you did.

1009
00:44:48,481 --> 00:44:50,481
Look, I know
what you're thinking.

1010
00:44:50,601 --> 00:44:52,521
But it's one possible future.

1011
00:44:52,641 --> 00:44:54,001
It's one timeline.

1012
00:44:55,081 --> 00:44:58,001
You want me to tell you
that Earth's going to be OK?

1013
00:44:58,121 --> 00:44:59,441
Cos I can't.

1014
00:45:00,721 --> 00:45:03,761
In your time, humanity is busy
arguing over the washing-up

1015
00:45:03,881 --> 00:45:05,841
while the house burns down.

1016
00:45:05,961 --> 00:45:09,241
Unless people face facts
and change,

1017
00:45:09,361 --> 00:45:11,201
catastrophe is coming.

1018
00:45:12,961 --> 00:45:14,481
But it's not decided.

1019
00:45:15,921 --> 00:45:17,761
You know that.

1020
00:45:17,881 --> 00:45:19,681
The future is not fixed.

1021
00:45:19,801 --> 00:45:23,401
It depends on billions
of decisions, and actions,

1022
00:45:23,521 --> 00:45:25,841
and people stepping up.

1023
00:45:27,121 --> 00:45:29,041
Humans.

1024
00:45:29,161 --> 00:45:32,241
I think you forget
how powerful you are.

1025
00:45:32,361 --> 00:45:34,921
Lives change worlds.

1026
00:45:35,041 --> 00:45:37,801
People can save planets,
or wreck them.

1027
00:45:37,921 --> 00:45:39,761
That's the choice.

1028
00:45:39,881 --> 00:45:41,441
Be the best of humanity.

1029
00:45:43,201 --> 00:45:44,441
Or...

1030
00:45:45,481 --> 00:45:46,641
(SNARLS)

1031
00:45:46,761 --> 00:45:49,361
(ROARS)

1032
00:46:21,641 --> 00:46:22,841
DOCTOR: Gilded Age, New York.

1033
00:46:22,961 --> 00:46:25,241
This is when
the modern world begins.

1034
00:46:25,361 --> 00:46:26,441
It's only Nikola Tesla!

1035
00:46:26,561 --> 00:46:29,081
The Niagara generator
should be shut down.

1036
00:46:29,201 --> 00:46:30,561
You believe this is alien?

